post_cb({"18310386": {"ParentId": "18310297", "CommentCount": "5", "Body": "<p>Yes it can:</p>\n<pre><code>class Y\n{\npublic:\n     Y();\n};\nclass X\n{\nprivate:\n     void foo() {}  \n     friend Y::Y();\n};\nY::Y() \n{\n   X x; x.foo(); \n}  \n</code></pre>\n<p>As per <strong>11.3 Friends [class.friend]</strong></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_18310297_18310386_0\">5) When a friend declaration refers to an overloaded name or operator, only the function specified by the parameter types becomes a friend. <strong>A\n  member function of a class X can be a friend of a class Y.</strong></p>\n<p id=\"so_18310297_18310386_1\">[ Example:</p>\n</blockquote>\n<pre><code>class Y {\nfriend char* X::foo(int);\nfriend X::X(char); // constructors can be friends\nfriend X::~X(); // destructors can be friends\n};\n</code></pre>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_18310297_18310386_2\">\u2014end example ]</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>(emphasis mine)</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "673730", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "18310386", "Score": "30", "CreationDate": "2013-08-19T09:22:05.063", "LastActivityDate": "2013-08-19T09:22:05.063"}, "18310297": {"CommentCount": "5", "ViewCount": "5227", "LastActivityDate": "2013-08-19T09:22:05.063", "Body": "<p>Can we declare constructor of a class to be friend? I think it cannot be. But i read somewhere that it can be, but i was unable to do. If yes can you please provide some example code.</p>\n", "PostTypeId": "1", "AcceptedAnswerId": "18310386", "FavoriteCount": "3", "Title": "Can a constructor function be a friend in c++?", "Id": "18310297", "Score": "24", "CreationDate": "2013-08-19T09:17:34.750", "Tags": "<c++>", "OwnerUserId": "1395384", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_18310297_18310386_0": {"section_id": 6688, "quality": 1.0, "length": 19}}, "n3337": {"so_18310297_18310386_0": {"section_id": 6443, "quality": 1.0, "length": 19}}, "n4659": {"so_18310297_18310386_0": {"section_id": 8163, "quality": 1.0, "length": 19}}}});